---
title: Sweet Chili Beef & Cabbage Stir-Fry with Rice, Cashews & Crispy Fried Onions
description: Forget takeout: The path to sweet-and-savory dinner bliss is only 15 quick minutes away! In this recipe, ground beef, shredded carrots, and cabbage are coated in a sumptuous sweet chili–soy sauce glaze. Everything comes together over a bed of fluffy quick-cooking rice with a crunchy garnish of cashews and crispy fried onions.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/67325e10ba08659748634757-19314614.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/67325e10ba08659748634757-en-US.pdf
course: main course
cuisine: East Asia
nutrition:
  calories: 860 kcal
  fat: 45 g
  saturated fat: 15 g
  carbohydrates: 74 g
  sugar: 26 g
  protein: 31 g
  fiber: 1 g
  sodium: 1220 mg
author: Sara Heilman
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sweet-chili-beef-and-cabbage-stir-fry-67325e10ba08659748634757
servings: 2
time required: 15 minutes
---

Wash and dry produce.

Roughly chop @cashews{1/2%oz}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in a large, preferably nonstick, pan
over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%oz}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, a
pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces,
until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. TIP: If there's excess grease in your pan,
carefully pour it out.

Stir in @red cabbage and carrot mix{4%oz}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%oz},
@sweet soy glaze{4%tbsp}, @ponzu sauce{12%ml}, and @water{1/4%cup}. Continue to
cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce has thickened and cabbage is tender,
~{2-3%minutes}. TIP: If sauce seems too thick, stir in a splash of water.

Massage @microwavable rice{1%unit} in package to break up grains; open package
and transfer to a medium #microwave-safe bowl{}. Add @water{3%tbsp} and cover
tightly with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave for ~{90%seconds}. Carefully uncover and
add @butter{1/2%tbsp}; stir until butter has melted.

> Microwave times may vary.

Divide rice and stir-fry between shallow #bowls{} in separate sections. Top
stir-fry with @crispy fried onions{1} and cashews. Serve.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.